{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:genesis.36",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Genesis 36 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:1",
      "text": "And these are the generations of Esau, the same is Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:2",
      "text": "Esau took wives of the daughters of Chanaan: Ada the daughter of Elon the Hethite, and Oolibama the daughter of Ana, the daughter of Sebeon the Hevite:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:3",
      "text": "And Basemath, the daughter of Ismael, sister of Nabajoth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:4",
      "text": "And Ada bore Eliphaz: Basemath bore Rahuel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:5",
      "text": "Oolibama bore Jehus, and Ihelon, and Core. These are the sons of Esau, that were born to him in the land of Chanaan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:6",
      "text": "And Esau took his wives, and his sons and daughters, and every soul of his house, and his substance, and cattle, and all that he was able to acquire in the land of Chanaan: and went into another country, and departed from his brother Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:7",
      "text": "For they were exceeding rich, and could not dwell together: neither was the land in which they sojourned able to bear them, for the multitude of their flocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:8",
      "text": "And Esau dwelt in mount Seir: he is Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:9",
      "text": "And these are the generations of Esau, the father of Edom, in mount Seir.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:10",
      "text": "And these the names of his sons: Eliphaz the son of Ada, the wife of Esau: and Rahuel, the son of Basemath, his wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:11",
      "text": "And Eliphaz had sons: Theman, Omar, Sepho, and Gatham and Cenez.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:12",
      "text": "And Thamna was the concubine of Eliphaz, the son of Esau: and she bore him Amalech. These are the sons of Ada, the wife of Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:13",
      "text": "And the sons of Rahuel were Nahath and Zara, Samma and Meza. These were the sons of Basemath, the wife of Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:14",
      "text": "And these were the sons of Oolibama, the daughter of Ana, the daughter of Sebeon, the wife of Esau, whom she bore to him, Jehus, and Ihelon, and Core.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:15",
      "text": "These were dukes of the sons of Esau: the sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn of Esau: duke Theman, duke Omar, duke Sepho, duke Cenez,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:16",
      "text": "Duke Core, duke Gatham, duke Amalech: these are the sons of Eliphaz, in the land of Edom, and these the sons of Ada.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:17",
      "text": "And these were the sons of Rahuel, the son of Esau: duke Nahath, duke Zara, duke Samma, duke Meza. And these are the dukes of Rahuel, in the land of Edom: these the sons of Basemath, the wife of Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:18",
      "text": "And these the sons of Oolibama, the wife of Esau: duke Jehus, duke Ihelon, duke Core. These are the dukes of Oolibama, the daughter of Ana, and wife of Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:19",
      "text": "These are the sons of Esau, and these the dukes of them: the same is Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:20",
      "text": "These are the sons of Seir, the Horrite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan, and Sobal, and Sebeon, and Ana,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:21",
      "text": "And Dison, and Eser, and Disan. These are dukes of the Horrites, the sons of Seir, in the land of Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:22",
      "text": "And Lotan had sons: Hori and Heman. And the sister of Lotan was Thamna.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:23",
      "text": "And these the sons of Sobal: Alvan, and Manahat, and Ebal, and Sepho, and Onam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:24",
      "text": "And these the sons of Sebeon: Aia and Ana. This is Ana that found the hot waters in the wilderness, when he fed the asses of Sebeon, his father:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:25",
      "text": "And he had a son Dison, and a daughter Oolibama.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:26",
      "text": "And these were the sons of Dison: Hamdan, and Eseban, and Jethram, and Charan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:27",
      "text": "These also were the sons of Eser: Balaan, and Zavan, and Acan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:28",
      "text": "And Dison had sons: Hus and Aram.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:29",
      "text": "These were dukes of the Horrites: duke Lotan, duke Sobal, duke Sebeon, duke Ana,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:30",
      "text": "Duke Dison, duke Eser, duke Disan: these were dukes of the Horrites that ruled in the land of Seir.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:31",
      "text": "And the kings that ruled in the land of Edom, before the children of Israel had a king, were these:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:32",
      "text": "Bela the son of Beor, and the name of his city Denaba.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:33",
      "text": "And Bela died, and Jobab, the son of Zara, of Bosra, reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:34",
      "text": "And when Jobab was dead, Husam, of the land of the Themanites, reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:35",
      "text": "And after his death, Adad, the son of Badad, reigned in his stead, who defeated the Madianites in the country of Boab; and the name of his city was Avith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:36",
      "text": "And when Adad was dead, there reigned in his stead, Semla, of Masreca.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:37",
      "text": "And he being dead, Saul, of the river Rohoboth, reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:38",
      "text": "And when he also was dead, Balanan, the son of Achobor, succeeded to the kingdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:39",
      "text": "This man also being dead, Adar reigned in his place; and the name of his city was Phau: and his wife was called Meetabel, the daughter of Matred, daughter of Mezaab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:40",
      "text": "And these are the names of the dukes of Esau in their kindreds, and places, and callings: duke Thamna, duke Alva, duke Jetheth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:41",
      "text": "Duke Oolibama, duke Ela, duke Phinon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:42",
      "text": "Duke Cenez, duke Theman, duke Mabsar,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:genesis.36.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:43",
      "text": "Duke Magdiel, duke Hiram: these are the dukes of Edom dwelling in the land of their government; the same is Esau, the father of the Edomites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
